  "summary": "Malicious code in polymarket-onchain-plugin (npm)",
  "details": "A supply-chain implant masked as a Polymarket on-chain utility for USDC and CTF allowances. When installed and required, it exfiltrates system information (OS, IP, username) and.env file contents (database URLs, Stripe secret keys, JWT secrets) to hxxps://api.fivefingerz[.]dev via POST requests to /api/validate/system-info and /api/validate/files. The approveUSDCAllowance function contains an eval(atob(...)) payload that sends the user's Ethereum private key to a Telegram bot as a second exfiltration channel.",
